{"abstract":[{"text":"Update your code to make use of the new state sharing tools in the library, such as the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Shared"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"property wrapper, and the "},{"code":"appStorage","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"fileStorage"},{"type":"text","text":" persistence strategies."}],"sections":[],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.10"},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/composablearchitecture\/migratingto1.10"]}],"seeAlsoSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.17.1","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.17","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.16","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.15","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.14","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.13","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.12","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.11","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.9","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.8","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.7","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.6","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.5","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.4"],"generated":true}],"kind":"article","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigrationGuides"]]},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"ComposableArchitecture"}],"roleHeading":"Article","title":"Migrating to 1.10","role":"article"},"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"level":2,"text":"Overview","type":"heading","anchor":"Overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The Composable Architecture is under constant development, and we are always looking for ways to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"simplify the library, and make it more powerful. This version of the library only introduced new"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"APIs and did not deprecate any existing APIs."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"aside","style":"important","name":"Important","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Before following this migration guide be sure you have fully migrated to the newest"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"tools of version 1.9. See "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigrationGuides","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" for more information."}]}]},{"text":"Sharing state","anchor":"Sharing-state","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The new tools added are concerned with allowing one to seamlessly share state with many parts of an"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"application that is easy to understand, and most importantly, testable. See the dedicated"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/SharingState","isActive":true},{"text":" article for more information on how to use these new tools.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To share state in one feature with another feature, simply use the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Shared"},{"text":" property wrapper:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["@ObservableState","struct State {","  @Shared var signUpData: SignUpData","  \/\/ ...","}"]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This will require that ","type":"text"},{"code":"SignUpData","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" be passed in from the parent, and any changes made to this state","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"will be instantly observed by all features holding onto it.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Further, there are persistence strategies one can employ in "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@Shared"},{"type":"text","text":". For example, if you want any"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"changes of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"signUpData"},{"type":"text","text":" to be automatically persisted to the file system you can use"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"fileStorage(_:decoder:encoder:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and specify a URL:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["@ObservableState","struct State {","  @Shared(.fileStorage(URL(\/* ... *\/) var signUpData = SignUpData()","  \/\/ ...","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Upon app launch the "},{"code":"signUpData","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" will be populated from disk, and any changes made to ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"signUpData"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"will automatically be persisted to disk. Further, if the disk version changes, all instances of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"signUpData","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" in the application will automatically update.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"There is another persistence strategy for storing simple data types in user defaults, called"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"appStorage"},{"text":". It can refer to a value in user defaults by a string","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"key:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["@ObservableState ","struct State {","  @Shared(.appStorage(\"isOn\")) var isOn = false","  \/\/ ...","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Similar to ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"fileStorage(_:decoder:encoder:)"},{"text":", upon launch of the application the initial","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"value of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"isOn"},{"type":"text","text":" will be populated from user defaults, and any change to "},{"code":"isOn","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" will be automatically"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"persisted to user defaults. Further, if the user defaults value changes, all instances of ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"isOn"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"in the application will automatically update."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"That is the basics of sharing data. Be sure to see the dedicated ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/SharingState","type":"reference"},{"text":" article","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"for more detailed information."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"references":{"doc://ComposableArchitecture/documentation/ComposableArchitecture":{"url":"\/documentation\/composablearchitecture","title":"ComposableArchitecture","type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"The Composable Architecture (TCA, for short) is a library for building applications in a consistent","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"and understandable way, with composition, testing, and ergonomics in mind. It can be used in","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"SwiftUI, UIKit, and more, and on any Apple platform (iOS, macOS, tvOS, and watchOS)."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture","kind":"symbol","role":"collection"},"doc://ComposableArchitecture/documentation/ComposableArchitecture/WithViewStore":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A view helper that transforms a "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/Store"},{"text":" into a ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/ViewStore"},{"text":" so that its state can be observed","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"by a view builder."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/WithViewStore","deprecated":true,"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/composablearchitecture\/withviewstore","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"WithViewStore"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"WithViewStore","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"WithViewStore"},"doc://ComposableArchitecture/documentation/ComposableArchitecture/MigratingTo1.13":{"type":"topic","role":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.13","kind":"article","title":"Migrating to 1.13","url":"\/documentation\/composablearchitecture\/migratingto1.13","abstract":[{"text":"The Composable Architecture now provides first class tools for building features in UIKit,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"including minimal state observation, presentation and stack navigation.","type":"text"}]},"doc://ComposableArchitecture/documentation/ComposableArchitecture/ForEachStore":